Thank you.

45:23.320 --> 45:28.320
The only thing I can say about like salaries and things, in my experience,

45:28.360 --> 45:36.360
that's more tied to geographic locations rather than, and well, the, the job role itself.

45:36.360 --> 45:41.360
Like if you're at a hyperscaler and I don't know VP position,

45:41.360 --> 45:45.360
then I assume you will not have money problems for the rest of your life.

45:45.360 --> 45:54.360
But, but at the same time, I, I really, my experience is I moved geographic locations and that affected my salary more than anything else.

45:54.400 --> 45:59.400
I have not noticed a difference.

45:59.400 --> 46:07.400
And to the, I have not to the degree that when I was putting my son through college and I very much focused on salary, which I don't anymore.

46:07.400 --> 46:10.400
But I was like 1% working on fully open source.

46:10.400 --> 46:12.400
Like I was in the 1%.

46:12.400 --> 46:17.400
Like fully open source, like nothing, like no proprietary software.

46:17.400 --> 46:20.400
So it's not, it does have a lot to do with the company.

46:20.400 --> 46:23.400
Different companies have different salary bands.

46:23.440 --> 46:32.440
So you're more likely to get more if you work at a big company and then a small startup startups tend to be a bit more weighted towards like stock options.

46:32.440 --> 46:34.440
So it just happens.

46:34.440 --> 46:39.440
But yeah, there isn't, there isn't really a difference whether it's open source or not.

46:39.440 --> 46:40.440
Yeah.

46:40.440 --> 46:49.440
And then I mean also comparing like, because I just asked this question because I worked at a foundation working at nonprofit versus like a for profit organizations.

46:49.480 --> 46:52.480
When they need to hire people, they need to be competitive.

46:52.480 --> 46:55.480
Like, I mean, if you're a nonprofit, you can offer like stock options.

46:55.480 --> 47:00.480
That's not viable, but they have to find other ways to make it appealing to attract good people.

47:00.480 --> 47:01.480
Right.

47:01.480 --> 47:05.480
So you can't be at a complete disadvantage like salary wise as an example.

47:05.480 --> 47:10.480
If that's, if, you know, that's, you know, that's my experience.

